"{\"uid\": \"kcbd.com-2024-07-25-lubbock-texas-roadhouse-hosting-tip-a-cop-event-benefiting-special-olympics\", \"text\": \"LUBBOCK, Texas (PRESS RELEASE) - As Special Olympics Texas races into the final heats of summer sports, Lubbock's Texas Roadhouse teams up with local police to raise money for the state-wide organization. The fundraiser is part of a state-wide effort with dozens of other Texas Roadhouse locations holding fundraisers the same week.  Police officers will help serve guests at the \\\"Tip-A-Cop\\\" event and collect donations.  Over the past fifteen years,Texas Roadhouse restaurants across the state have raised more than $1,984,600 at this event for Special Olympics.  When:\\u00a0Thursday, July 25 from 5:00 - 9:00 p.m.  Where:\\u00a0Texas Roadhouse located at 6101 Slide Rd.  Why:\\u00a0Texas Roadhouse has a continuous history of giving back to its communities.\\u00a0 In this case, 100% of all donations will go directly to Special Olympics Texas.  Copyright 2024 KCBD. All rights reserved.\"}"